 - **Gradio:** Use i18n system, follow component patterns, proper state management.
 - **Gradio References:** https://www.gradio.app/docs - Components, State, Event Listeners.
+- **Gradio 6 reference implementation (battle-tested):** In the sibling **cmw-rag** repo, **`rag_engine/api/app.py`** (https://github.com/arterm-sedov/cmw-rag). Prefer aligning tricky Gradio 6 behavior with that file before inventing new patterns: build **`gr.Blocks`**, register **`gr.api`** endpoints inside the context, call **`demo.queue(...)`** after the Blocks/API wiring (before **`mount_gradio_app`** when embedding), use **`queue=False`** on short UI-only `.success`/`.then` chains, set **`concurrency_limit`** on the heavy streaming handler, mark internal listeners with **`api_visibility="private"`**, and expose static/theme paths via **`allowed_paths`** / **`css_paths`** on mount or **`launch()`** as applicable.
+- **Gradio UI bisect (dev only):** For local hangs (tabs/sidebar/timers/downloads chains), set in the shell or local **`.env`**—not in **`.env.example`**: **`CMW_UI_TABS`**, **`CMW_UI_TAB_LIMIT`** (e.g. **`3`** = home + chat + logs only), **`CMW_UI_STACK_HOME_CHAT`**, **`CMW_UI_DISABLE_AUTO_TIMERS`** (see **`agent_ng/agent_config.py`**). Explicit **`CMW_UI_TABS`** wins over **`CMW_UI_TAB_LIMIT`**. **`CMW_UI_TABS=home,chat` alone still uses `gr.Tabs` (you will see a tab bar)**; add **`CMW_UI_STACK_HOME_CHAT=true`** to drop the tab bar and stack sections in one column. Chat→downloads **`.then`** runs only when the downloads tab is included. Changing these vars in the same process rebuilds **`demo`** via a signature check in **`get_demo_with_language_detection()`**.
 
